ce:section.ce:para:
In view of outstanding extraction capacity, we developed an analysis method to determine trace OCPs from water based on CDs/RGO SPME coating coupled with GC–MS. The analytical performances of developed method were validated in terms of linearity, relative standard deviations (RSDs), limits of detection (LODs), and limits of quantitation (LOQs). As listed in Table 1
                        , the developed method presented good linearity for seven OCPs in the concentration range of 0.05–2500 ng/L with linear coefficients (R2) of 0.9864–0.9976. The LODs and LOQs were calculated based on the standard deviation of the response (δ) and the slope (S) of the calibration curve at the levels approaching the limits according to equation LOD = 3 (δ/S) and LOQ = 10 (δ/S), with results that the LODs and LOQs for seven OCPs are in the range of 0.003–0.051 ng/L and 0.01–0.169 ng/L, respectively. The RSDs for one fiber are ranging from 4.5 % to 12.4 % within five replications, and RSDs for five fibers vary from 6.7 % to 14.6 %. In comparison to other method reported in the literatures, the proposed method exhibits superior performances in terms of LODs and LOQs (Table 2
                        ). High sensitivity, wide linearity, and excellent reproducibility make the proposed method a great potential for determination of trace OCPs from water.
